sense.name: hide from view; eclipse
sense.examples: The moon will completely occult the sun for 6 minutes, 39 seconds. That will be occulted about a minute after the primary star in a region. The lids were occulting her eyes. The beam of light occults every so often. Callisto disappears even though it misses being occulted by Jupiter. The target star was not occulted from your site.
